 Society\n.'),(231,'https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=10154886141978894&set=a.118071123893.124938.577163893&type=1&theater',49,'In the past few days, I have received... - Erin Smith Chieze | Facebook',0.22784,0.98952,0.77216,'Her \npost\n with the 15-year-old image has now been shared nearly 42,000 times.'),(232,'https://www.facebook.com/CNNHealth',49,'CNN Health - Home | Facebook',0.33929,0.14553,0.66071,'See the latest news and share your comments with CNN Health on\n Facebook\n and \nTwitter\n.'),(233,'https://twitter.com/cnnhealth',49,'CNN Health (@cnnhealth) | Twitter',0.33929,0.14553,0.66071,'See the latest news and share your comments with CNN Health on\n Facebook\n and \nTwitter\n.'),(234,'http://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamasurgery/article-abstract/2613702',48,'couldn\'t fetch title',0.62229,0.85518,0.37771,'Younger women with breast cancer are increasingly opting to undergo double mastectomies, even if they were diagnosed with early-stage cancer in only one breast, known as unilateral breast cancer, according to a study \npublished in the journal JAMA Surgery\n on Wednesday. '),(235,'http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/14/showbiz/angelina-jolie-double-mastectomy/',48,'Angelina Jolie undergoes double mastectomy - CNN.com',0.77876,0.95379,0.22124,'\"Another factor is probably the \nAngelina Jolie effect\n. She was diagnosed with the BRCA-1 cancer gene that mutation that causes breast cancer, and she had a double mastectomy, so that was covered widely in the media,\" he said. \"For women diagnosed with breast cancer in one breast, there is no evidence to suggest to remove the unaffected breast.\"'),(236,'http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/tbj.12648/full',48,'Differences between Breast Conservation-Eligible Patients and Unilateral Mastectomy Patients in Choosing Contralateral Prophylactic Mastectomies - Sabel - 2016 - The Breast Journal - Wiley Online Library',0.38847,0.81127,0.61153,'Sabel and his colleagues found in a separate study that the percentage 