ct Sheet - National Cancer Institute\r\n',0.30030,0.91454,0.69970,'Even if a \nCPM procedure is to prevent cancer\n \nfrom developing in the healthy breast\n, Jemal said, \"the maximum is 6% of women will develop breast cancer on the unaffected breast within the next 10 years. It is very small.\"'),(242,'http://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/volumes/65/wr/mm6540a1.htm',50,'Patterns and Trends in Age-Specific Black-White Differences in Breast Cancer Incidence and Mortality – United States, 1999–2014\r\n\n\n | MMWR\n\n',0.45733,0.89060,0.54267,' (CNN)\nRacial disparities between black and white breast cancer patients are receding, according to a report released Thursday. Younger women of both races benefit equally from timely treatment, but differences in death rates still exist for black and white women over age 50, a \nnew report from the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention \nindicates.'),(243,'http://www.cdc.gov/cancer/breast/basic_info/screening.htm',50,'CDC - What Is Breast Cancer Screening?',0.57725,0.82455,0.42275,'Cancer can usually be found at a much earlier stage when screening guidelines are followed: All women, beginning at 50, need to get a mammogram every other year, while women with a family history of breast cancer should consult with their doctors about earlier mammograms, according to \nUS Preventative Services Task Force\n recommendations. '),(244,'https://nccd.cdc.gov/uscs/',50,'\r\n	United States Cancer Statistics\r\n',0.39045,0.99978,0.60955,'Led by Dr. Lisa Richardson, director of the Division of Cancer Prevention and Control, the CDC researchers examined rates of breast cancer occurrence in women between 1999 and 2013 and rates of breast cancer deaths between 2000 and 2014, using data from the \nUnited States Cancer Statistics\n report. '),(245,'https://www.facebook.com/CNNHealth',50,'CNN Health - Home | Facebook',0.33929,0.14553,0.66071,'See the latest news and share your comments with CNN Health on\n Facebook\n and \nTwitter\n.'),(246,'https://tw