ection, two are likely to result in a bump (points No. 1 and No. 5), one probably won’t (No. 3) — and two aren’t clear (No. 2 and No. 4). If you’re looking for some tiebreakers, Baker and Oneal’s study found that the average foreign policy entanglement results in an approval rating jump of just 0.1 percentage points. And \nduring the Obama administration\n, the only event that produced any rally-around-the-flag effect was the killing of Osama bin Laden. And that effect lasted just a month.'),(721,'http://www.washingtonpost.com/sf/national/2015/07/15/from-a-first-arrest-to-a-life-sentence/?utm_term=.a9f81ed69003',109,'How a first crack cocaine offense led to a life sentence  | The Washington Post',0.35754,0.78061,0.64246,'[\nFrom a first arrest to a life sentence\n]'),(722,'https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/sessions-vows-crackdown-on-violent-crime-in-first-major-speech-as-attorney-general/2017/02/27/b18af654-fd42-11e6-8f41-ea6ed597e4ca_story.html?utm_term=.a29b16af904e',109,' Sessions vows crackdown on violent crime in first major speech as attorney general - The Washington Post',0.42109,0.75380,0.57891,'[\nSessions vows crackdown on violent crime in first major speech as attorney general\n]'),(723,'https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/obama-grants-final-330-commutations-to-nonviolent-drug-offenders/2017/01/19/41506468-de5d-11e6-918c-99ede3c8cafa_story.html?utm_term=.623bca10d66b',109,' Obama grants final 330 commutations to nonviolent drug offenders - The Washington Post',0.20192,0.83410,0.79808,'Obama, the first sitting president to visit a federal prison, launched an ambitious\n clemency initiative\n to release certain drug offenders from prison early. And Holder told his prosecutors, in an effort to make punishments more fairly fit the crime, to stop charging low-level nonviolent drug offenders with offenses that imposed severe mandatory sentences. He called his strategy, outlined in an August 2013 report, \n“Smart on Crime.